ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I will recommend this course.

A ton of work but you learn a lot. I would recommend it to students that could use this information for the future. I think people shouldn't take it if it won't apply to their research because it is a big time commitment.
I would totally recommend this course, the name of the course is not very exciting but I feel it's an extremely useful course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have never learned any of these techniques before. Very useful for future research I may do.

Applying numerical methods to solve any kind of equation is an inherent part of my research. I deal with equations and aim to solve them using sofwares such as MATLAB. With my newly gained understanding of how to apply numerical methods to a problem, I can define error bounds, tolerances, different methods to solve a problem.
